# 🏨 Hotel Booking Database Analysis

This project analyzes hotel booking data using SQL. It explores guest behavior, revenue performance, and booking patterns in a simulated hospitality database.

## 📁 Project Structure

- `database/hotel_booking_db.sql` — SQL script to create the database and insert sample data
- `insights/` — SQL queries for extracting business insights
- `ERD/` — Entity Relationship Diagram of the database

## 📊 Key Insights

### 📌 Booking Performance
- Total revenue generated
- Revenue by room type
- Average booking value

### 👤 Guest Behavior
- Top 5 guests by frequency
- Guests with highest spending
- Countries with the most bookings

### 🗓️ Booking Trends
- Monthly booking patterns
- Channel analysis (Online, Walk-in, etc.)
- Most booked room types

## 🧱 Database Schema

- `guest(guest_id, first_name, last_name, country, email)`
- `room(room_id, room_type, price_per_night, capacity, hotel_branch)`
- `bookings(booking_id, guest_id, room_id, check_in_date, check_out_date, booking_date, total_amount, booking_channel)`

## 🔗 Relationships

- `bookings.guest_id → guest.guest_id`
- `bookings.room_id → room.room_id`

## 🧰 Tools Used

- SQL (PostgreSQL)
- DB Browser for SQLite (or any SQL IDE)

